name: Cukui Art Series
description: Since the mid-80s, when Orly Locquiao was first introduced to graffiti, his attention to lines, shapes, and curvatures in abstract form became second nature to him. While attending the Art Institute of Illinois in Chicago for graphic design, Orly began his first tattoo apprenticeship with Mike Cruz in 1996 and later moved to Hawaii where he met his teachers Po’oino Yrondi and Aisea Toetu’u that taught him the roots of Polynesian and South Pacific tattooing. Known for his intricate tribal tattoos, Orly wanted to express his art through tee designs as well, and launched Cukui in 2008 - a clothing brand with sub-cultural influences in South Pacific tattoos, Chicano lifestyle, graffiti, and photography. Larger image here. Each limited-edition piece comes in Hawaiian Koa. There are only 300 pieces available, so pick one up before they're gone!

name: Curly Figured Cherry
description:
Curly Figured Cherry, also known as Prunus Serotina, is a tree found widely throughout the United States and Canada, primarily desired for its wood, fruit and ornamental blossoms. A member of the Prunus family, its wood varies from a yellowish pink when first cut to a deep, rich reddish brown. Cherry wood is very desirable and commonly used in furniture and cabinetry. The variety we employ in our iPhone 4/4S backs is curly figured, producing a timber that has slightly wavy darker vertical grain with loops and swirls found randomly throughout. After sanding and finishing, Curly Figured Cherry is smooth with light apparent grain, offering a surface that will not fingerprint while still offering superior durability and feel.

Comes with one complete pre-assembled iPhone 4/4S replacement back, illustrated instruction guide, Pentalobe screwdriver, #00 Phillips-head screwdriver (if needed) and screen protector.

name: Makore Fiddleback
description:
Makore Fiddleback, also known as African Cherry, is a sturdy hardwood native to Western and Middle Africa from Sierra Leone to Gabon. The timber itself is relatively straight-grained and brownish red with beautiful wavy diagonal veining running at a slight angle to the vertical grain pattern. Makore is the material of choice for many ornate applications such as furniture inlays, high-end joinery, turning and fine boat interiors. The Fiddleback variety we employ in our iPhone 4/4S backs gets its name from frequent use in violin making. After sanding and finishing, Makore Fiddleback is smooth with moderate apparent grain, offering a surface that will not fingerprint while still offering superior durability and feel.

Comes with one complete pre-assembled iPhone 4/4S replacement back, illustrated instruction guide, Pentalobe screwdriver, #00 Phillips-head screwdriver (if needed) and screen protector.

name: Birdseye Maple
description:
There are 129 different species of Maple - most of which are native to Asia, with certain species also being found throughout Europe, North Africa and North America. Maple has long been used in the United States for a variety of items, from baseball bats and bowling pins to fine furniture and musical instruments, desirable for its distinctive honey-colored glow and strength. The variety we employ in our iPhone 4/4S backs is North American Sugar Maple with a Birdseye pattern - a phenomenon that occurs only in select trees which resembles tiny swirled eyes mixed in with the grain pattern. After sanding and finishing, the texture of Birdseye Maple is smooth with little apparent grain, offering a surface that will not fingerprint while still offering superior durability and feel.

Comes with one complete pre-assembled iPhone 4/4S replacement back, illustrated instruction guide, Pentalobe screwdriver, #00 Phillips-head screwdriver (if needed) and screen protector.

name: Benny Gold Art Series
description: Benny Gold is literally a streetwear icon - lending his design prowess to such companies as Huf, Mash, Stussy, JanSport, Gravis, Carhartt Europe, Nike, Adidas, Real Skateboards, Ipath and DVS footwear to name a few. This in addition to his own Benny Gold brand of clothing and accessories has made the artist a notable fixture in the skateboarding and street wear world. We are very pleased to have the opportunity to offer the Benny Gold x Material6 collaboration Art Series back, which features a laser-engraved native design from the Valencia Collection in Curly Figured Cherry. name: Figueroa
description:
Figueroa, also known as Andiroba or Crabwood, is a tree native to Brazil primarily desired for its durability and medicinal uses. A member of the Mahogany family, its honeyed golden color and even grain pattern make it desirable for use in furniture, nautical decking and cabinetry. The variety we employ in our iPhone 4/4S backs is quartersawn, producing a timber that has slightly wavy darker vertical grain and light diagonal banding found throughout. After sanding and finishing, Figueroa is smooth with light apparent grain, offering a surface that will not fingerprint while still offering superior durability and feel.

Comes with one complete pre-assembled iPhone 4/4S replacement back, illustrated instruction guide, Pentalobe screwdriver, #00 Phillips-head screwdriver (if needed) and screen protector.

name: Lacewood
description:
Lacewood, also known as silky oak, is a tree native to Australia primarily desired for its highly figured wood and springtime ornamental yellow-orange flowers. The timber itself possesses one of the most unique grain patterns of all the exotic woods, most easily recognized by its large rays, which resemble living cellular cross sections under a microscope. As such, it is commonly used for elaborate inlays and decorative items such as jewelry boxes. The variety we employ in our iPhone 4/4S backs is quartersawn, producing an even grain that changes dramatically depending on ambient lighting. After sanding and finishing, Lacewood is smooth with moderate apparent grain, offering a surface that will not fingerprint while still offering superior durability and feel.

Comes with one complete pre-assembled iPhone 4/4S replacement back, illustrated instruction guide, Pentalobe screwdriver, #00 Phillips-head screwdriver (if needed) and screen protector.

name: Rock Maple
description:
Rock Maple, known to arborists as Acer Glabrum, is a smaller species of Maple commonly growing to no more than 32 feet tall found in abundance in the Rocky Mountain region of the United States. Primarily desired for its extreme hardness, Rock Maple is frequently cut into veneers and used in the manufacture of skateboard decks and certain piano brands. The variety we employ in our iPhone 4/4S backs is manufactured in the US and shipped to us in custom-dyed 52 layer blocks, which we then process in-house into 1mm thin solid panels. After sanding and finishing, Rock Maple is smooth with little apparent grain, offering a surface that will not fingerprint while still offering superior durability and feel.

Comes with one complete pre-assembled iPhone 4/4S replacement back, illustrated instruction guide, Pentalobe screwdriver, #00 Phillips-head screwdriver (if needed) and screen protector.

name: Rich Arbitelle Art Series
description: After getting his start in graffiti and pencil drawings, Atlanta-based artist Rich Arbitelle, who is primarily self-taught, has expanded his work to include paintings, ink drawings, apparel/skateboard graphic design, art boards, muscle car designs and photography. Inspired by his come-up in '90s New York City as a skateboarder, where he was featured in Larry Clark's 1995 cult classic Kids and co-owned the skateboard company Brooklyn Boards, Rich takes aspects of urban grittiness and blends them with renderings of the natural and spirit worlds, incorporating his Native American roots into his vision. His aesthetic is distinguished by intricate line work, haunting portraiture, and urban calligraphy. Larger image here. Each numbered and signed limited-edition piece comes in Birdseye Maple. There are only 300 pieces available, so pick one up before they're gone!

name: Custom Engraving
description: Add your own custom engraving to make your already unique Material6 iPhone 4 or iPhone 4S wood inlay back stand out even more. Simply add this item to your order, then download our engraving template here to get started designing your beautiful new one of a kind inlay. Don't worry if you're not a designer by trade or don't have sophisticated software on hand - just send us a high-quality image and we'll do the rest for you for free. There's no charge for us cleaning up and rendering your artwork... Not sure what you might like engraved? Check out our flickr page here for some ideas... All engravings are done on site with an extremely precise computer-controlled laser engraving machine that cuts even the tiniest of details. We're looking forward to seeing what you come up with! *Engraving on Black Walnut is extremely subtle - almost the same color as the wood itself. Please keep this in mind when placing your order*
